HEADWORD: Crural
<hw>Cru"ral</hw> <pr>(-r<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cruralis</ets>, fr. <ets>crus</ets>, <ets>cruris</ets>, leg: cf. F.
<ets>crural</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to
the thigh or leg, or to any of the parts called <xex>crura</xex>;
<as>as, the <ex>crural</ex> arteries; <ex>crural</ex> arch;
<ex>crural</ex> canal; <ex>crural</ex> ring</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crus</ent>⟦br⟧
